<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 6:28PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Craig,
west central Delaware and northeastern Mayes Counties through 700 PM
CDT...
At 628 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
east of Disney, moving west at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Vinita...                         Langley...
Ketchum...                        Spavinaw...
Disney...                         Pensacola...
Cherokee State Park...            Spavinaw State Park...
Chloeta...                        Cleora...
Strang...                         Disney Little Blue State Park...
Zena...
This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 284 and 285.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
